{
  "v": "2.0",
  "header": {
    "v": "0.1",
    "name": "AT-II 'Hardhat'",
    "gameVersion": "0.2.49.4",
    "mass": 30311,
    "creationDate": "1942.01.01",
    "class": "",
    "desc": "In the emergence of heavier mass produced vehicles, Beigee forsaw the need for a turreted tank destroyer. The result was the 'Hardhat', named so for its large distinct well protected turret. Also known as the self propelled bunker turret, the Hardhat is designed to sit in a hull-down position, aided by its short hull, picking off enemy armor from great distance while remaining impenetrable itself."
  },
